6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Cursor and Tabnine share a solid foundation of core features including Autocomplete, Code Generation, Refactoring, Test Generation. Where Cursor pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Review and Debugging and Documentation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Tabnine uniquely offers Ide Integration, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Cursor holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Tabnine scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Tabnine comes in at a lower starting price of $12/mo, while Cursor begins at $20/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Cursor's free tier and Tabnine's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
