a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Cursor is best suited for developers wanting an AI native editor, rapid prototyping, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Tabnine, meanwhile, shines for privacy focused teams, enterprise with strict compliance, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Cursor describes itself as \"The AI-first code editor built for productivity.\" Tabnine, established in 2018, positions itself as \"AI assistant that runs on your private codebase securely.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Cursor** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 7), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Tabnine is a poor choice — far from it. Tabnine excels in its own right, particularly for privacy focused teams and enterprise with strict compliance.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value purpose-built ai editor experience, go with Cursor. If can run fully on-premise matters more to you, Tabnine is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
